Introduction

Jeon Minwook, also known as J-Min, is a South Korean rapper under PocketDol Studio. He is a member of the boy group BAE173 and the co-ed group A-SIX.

On September 26, 2024, he was announced as a contestant on JTBC's survival show PROJECT7, which began airing in October 2024. He successfully secured a spot in the final lineup, placing 3rd, and became a member of the group CLOSE YOUR EYES.
